  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I make a call in Jio sim?",
  "response": "Making a call with a Jio SIM card is quite straightforward. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Insert SIM Card**: Ensure your Jio SIM card is properly inserted into your phone. If you have a dual SIM phone, make sure you know which slot the Jio SIM is in.\n\n2. **Power On**: Turn on your phone.\n\n3. **Network Connection**: Confirm that your phone is connected to the Jio network. You should see the network bars and \"Jio 4G\" on the notification panel.\n\n4. **Dial Number**: Open the dialer app on your phone. Enter the phone number you wish to call, including the appropriate country code if necessary.\n\n5. **Initiate Call**: Press the call button (usually a green phone icon) to start the call.\n\n6. **VoLTE Support**: Ensure your phone supports VoLTE (Voice over LTE), as Jio primarily uses 4G for both internet and voice calls. Most modern smartphones support VoLTE.\n\n7. **Activate Jio Services**: If this is your first time using the Jio SIM, make sure the SIM is activated. You should have received an activation message from Jio upon inserting the SIM card.\n\n8. **Check Balance**: Ensure you have sufficient balance and an active plan. You can check the balance via the MyJio app.\n\n9. **App Calls**: Alternatively, you can make calls using the JioCall app if you have the necessary data plan active.\n\nIf there are any issues, you might want to check your network settings, restart your phone, or contact Jio customer support for further assistance.",
